Sfinar Gourian was fined £15,000 after being found guilty of insulting the Egyptian flag . 
  She wore a tight dress in its red, white and black color scheme during a performance in 2013 . 
  The court in Agouza sentenced her to six months in prison but she is expected to avoid jail time after paying £10,000 bail . 
  Insulting the flag was made illegal by decree under President Adly Mansour . 
 